                        <h1>Digital Imaging</h1>                                  
                        The digital imaging market continues to grow in 2008, as more young people purchase cameras, more consumers capture images and digital cameras look to go wireless (again). If digital imaging matters to you, you'll want to know what's happening in 2008 for the 2009 International CES: 
<UL>
<LI>Camera shipments break 100 million unit mark </LI>
<LI>DSLR category is getting bigger </LI>
<LI>DSLR users are bigger spenders </LI>
<LI>Camera phones are on the rise in the U.S. </LI>
<LI>GenZ is texting and taking more shots with camera phones </LI>
<LI>Digital dominates camcorder market </LI>
<LI>Media card sales soar as prices decline </LI>
<LI>Photo books gain momentum </LI>
<LI>Online photo printing shows steady growth</LI></UL><A href="/register">Register today for the 2009 International CES</A> to learn, network and investigate new technology emerging in the digital imaging industry and many other consumer technology markets. It's free if you sign up before November 1. <BR><BR><SPAN class=smallText><EM>Source: Digital America, a CEA publication.</EM></SPAN>

